```c
SemaphoreHandle_t xI2CMutex = xSemaphoreCreateMutex();

// Task A:
if (xSemaphoreTake(xI2CMutex, pdMS_TO_TICKS(100)) == pdTRUE) {
    i2c_read_sensor_a(data_a);
    xSemaphoreGive(xI2CMutex);
} else {
    // Timeout — handle error
}

// Task B:
if (xSemaphoreTake(xI2CMutex, pdMS_TO_TICKS(100)) == pdTRUE) {
    i2c_read_sensor_b(data_b);
    xSemaphoreGive(xI2CMutex);
}
```
Mutex provides priority inheritance to prevent priority inversion. Always use timeout (not portMAX_DELAY) in production. Never take a mutex from an ISR — use binary semaphore instead.

Cortex-M NVIC priority:
```c
// Set priority grouping: 4 bits preemption, 0 bits sub-priority
HAL_NVIC_SetPriorityGrouping(NVIC_PRIORITYGROUP_4);

// High priority (preempts others):
HAL_NVIC_SetPriority(TIM2_IRQn, 1, 0);  // Motor control
HAL_NVIC_SetPriority(EXTI0_IRQn, 2, 0); // Safety switch

// Medium priority:
HAL_NVIC_SetPriority(DMA1_Stream0_IRQn, 5, 0); // ADC DMA
HAL_NVIC_SetPriority(USART2_IRQn, 6, 0); // Communication

// Low priority (for FreeRTOS-compatible ISRs):
HAL_NVIC_SetPriority(TIM6_IRQn, 10, 0); // Background timing
```
Rule: Safety-critical > Real-time control > Communication > Background. FreeRTOS API only callable from priority >= configMAX_SYSCALL_INTERRUPT_PRIORITY.
